{
  "texts": [
    "While it does often ask interesting and challenging questions, the exercise does not mirror an actual teaching exercise in the classroom.",
    "As with any AI exercise assigned to students, expect variable responses from the AI.",
    "Students will have different experiences to share in class about this interaction.",
    "The act of breaking down your knowledge into sequential step by step instructions to explain something someone else helps you learn, and highlights gaps or inconsistencies in your own knowledge.",
    "For students this process may break the illusion of expertise (Glenberg, 1982): can you create something (in this case an explanation) for someone else?"
  ]
}